@Oxyntas - by definition, a collection labeled discography should include every studio/official release to the date of the collection.  There can be no "best", only whether it "is" or "is not" a discography.  Everything and anything else is a compilation, subject to the subjectivity of the listener who can classify it as ok, good, best, etc. Compilation of course being a collection of recordings by a single artist (or individual among several acts, a la John Fogerty, Slash, Ozzy, and of course MJK himself).  Technically, since Tool releases singles for radio promotion, this is NOT the discography as of 11/2006 as it is missing the Lateralus, Aenima and Undertow singles along with Vicarious (The Pot and Jambi had not yet been released, officially)
